public abstract class Manager<PullData,PushData>
extends java.lang.Object

receivePushData

protected abstract boolean receivePushData(PushData pushed)
Should use the received data to update itself accordingly.

Parameters:
pushed - The response from the pushed data.
Returns:
true if the push response is the same as the pull data. In this case receivePullData(Object) will do any processing. You should make absolutely sure here that PushData can be cast to PullData, as this is unchecked. I'm relying on you here!
